This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as part-of-speech tagging. It also uses neural networks, which are commonly used in this sub-field. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses machine learning techniques to learn from disparate sources of distant supervision. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as the paper uses neural networks to perform the part-of-speech tagging task. 

Finally, cs.DL (Deep Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper uses distributed representations, which are commonly used in deep learning.
